      "id": 1,
      "options": {"content": "# Observability Demo: Start Here\n\nUse this dashboard as the investigation menu. The instructor may activate a hidden scenario; dashboards intentionally show symptoms, not scenario flags.\n\n1. Open **01 Operations Overview** to decide whether the issue is latency, errors, traffic, or saturation.\n2. Open **02 Service Drilldown** when one service or replica looks suspicious.\n3. Open **03 Checkout Journey** when the user-facing `/shop` flow fails or slows down.\n4. Open **04 Logs, Traces, Profiles** when you have a trace ID or CPU looks high.\n5. Open **05 Symptom Investigation** for a side-by-side replica comparison.", "mode": "markdown"},
      "title": "Which Dashboard Should I Use?",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus"},
      "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"unit": "reqps"}, "overrides": []},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 7},
      "id": 2,
      "targets": [{"expr": "sum(rate(demo_http_requests_total[5m])) by (service)", "legendFormat": "{{service}}", "refId": "A"}],
      "title": "Traffic By Service",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus"},
      "fieldConfig": {"defaults": {"unit": "percentunit"}, "overrides": []},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 7},
      "id": 3,
      "targets": [{"expr": "sum(rate(demo_http_requests_total{status=~\"5..\"}[5m])) by (service) / clamp_min(sum(rate(demo_http_requests_total[5m])) by (service), 0.001)", "legendFormat": "{{service}}", "refId": "A"}],
      "title": "Error Ratio By Service",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
